                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 18: Insurance regulator IRDA has proposed to do away with the wide variance in charges imposed by insurers for surrendering Ulips. The move will further streamline the system governing these securities-linked products. IRDA said most insurers were following best global practices in Ulips. The insurance regulator is in a tussle with market watchdog Sebi over Ulip regulation.                             
	 New Delhi, May 18: An empowered group of ministers, headed by finance minister Pranab Mukherjee, is likely to meet early next month to decide on freeing petrol and diesel prices from government control. The panel will also consider ways to deal with revenue losses on selling domestic LPG and kerosene below cost.                            
	 New Delhi, May 18: Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) said Mahindra Satyam had kept its shareholders in the dark about its performance. There is no information available about the companys sales, earnings and employees, L amp;Ts top official said, adding that in the absence of information it was not able to decide when to sell stake in Mahindra Satyam.                             
	 New Delhi, May 18: Reliance Industries and RNRL today began informal talks for a possible gas supply agreement, in line with a Supreme Court verdict earlier this month on the row between Mukesh and Anil Ambani groups.                             
	 Calcutta, May 18: Electrosteel Castings has reported a 22. 27 per cent decline in net sales to Rs 1,428.77 crore in 2009-10 against Rs 1,838.04 crore in the previous year.                                                                                                                          
